ITS FUNCTION IS TO EXAMINE THE LOW 8 BITS<newline>OF CHANNEL 32 TO SEE IF ANY ISOLATION-VALVE CLOSURE BITS HAVE APPEARED OR DISAPPEARED (THE CREW IS WARNED OF JET<newline>FAILURES BY LAMPS LIT BY THE GRUMMAN FAILURE-DETECTION CIRCUITRY; THEY MAY RESPOND BY OPERATING SWITCHES WHICH<newline>ISOLATE PAIRS OF JETS FROM THE PROPELLANT TANKS AND SET BITS IN CHANNEL 32). IN THE EVENT THAT CHANNEL 32 BITS<newline>DIFFER FROM 'PVALVEST', THE RECORD OF ACTIONS TAKEN BY THIS ROUTINE, THE APPROPRIATE BITS IN 'CH5MASK' &<newline>'CH6MASK', USED BY THE DAP JET-SELECTION LOGIC, ARE UPDATED, AS IS 'PVALVEST'. THE HIGHEST-NUMBERED BIT IN CHANNEL 32 WHICH REQUIRES<newline>ACTION IS THE ONE PROCESSED.<newline>THE CODING IN THE FAILURE MONITOR HAS BEEN WRITTEN SO AS TO HAVE ALMOST COMPLETE RESTART PROTECTION. ONE CASE WHICH MAY BE SEEN TO EVADE PROTECTION IS THE OCCURRENCE OF A RESTART AFTER UPDATING<newline>ONE OR BOTH DAP MASK-WORDS BUT BEFORE UPDATING 'PVALVEST', COUPLED WITH A CHANGE IN THE VALVE-BIT BACK TO ITS<newline>FORMER STATE. e.description: PROGRAM NAME: TNONTEST.<newline>FUNCTIONAL DESCRIPTION: THIS PROGRAM HONORS REQUESTS FOR ISS INITIALIZATION. ISS TURN-ON (CHANNEL 30 BIT 14)<newline>AND ISS OPERATE (CHANNEL 30 BIT 9) REQUESTS ARE TREATED AS A PAIR AND PROCESSING TAKES PLACE .480 SECONDS<newline>AFTER EITHER ONE APPEARS. THIS INITIALIZATION TAKES ON ONE OF THE FOLLOWING THREE FORMS:<newline>1) ISS TURN-ON: IN THIS SITUATION THE COMPUTER IS OPERATING WHEN THE ISS IS TURNED ON. NOMINALLY,<newline>BOTH ISS TURN-ON AND ISS OPERATE APPEAR. THE PLATFORM IS CAGED FOR 90 SECONDS AND THE ICDU'S ZEROED<newline>SO THAT AT THE END OF THE PROCESS THE GIMBAL LOCK MONITOR WILL FUNCTION PROPERLY.<newline>2) ICDU INITIALIZATION: IN THIS CASE THE COMPUTER WAS PROBABLY TURNED ON WITH THE ISS IN OPERATE OR<newline>A FRESH START WAS DONE WITH THE ISS IN OPERATE. IN THIS CASE ONLY ISS OPERATE IS ON. THE ICDU'S ARE<newline>ZEROED SO THE GIMBAL LOCK MONITOR WILL FUNCTION. AN EXCEPTION IS IF THE ISS IS IN GIMBAL LOCK AFTER<newline>A RESTART, THE ICDU'S WILL NOT BE ZEROED.<newline>3) RESTART WITH RESTARTABLE PROGRAM USING THE IMU: IN THIS CASE, NO INITIALIZATION TAKES PLACE SINCE<newline>IT IS ASSUMED THAT THE USING PROGRAM DID THE INITIALIZATION AND THEREFORE T4RUPT SHOULD NOT INTERFERE.<newline>IMODES30 BIT 7 IS SET = 1 BY THE FIRST BIT (CHANNEL 30 BIT 14 OR 9) WHICH ARRIVES. FOLLOWING THIS. TNONTEST IS<newline>ENTERED, FINDS BIT 7 = 1 BUT BIT 8 = 0, SO IT SETS BIT 8 = 1 AND EXITS. THE NEXT TIME IT FINDS BIT 8 = 1 AND<newline>PROCEEDS, SETTING BITS 8 AND 7 = 0. AT PROCTNON, IF ISS TURN-ON REQUEST IS PRESENT, THE ISS IS CAGED (ZERO +<newline>COARSE). IF ISS OPERATE IS NOT PRESENT PROGRAM ALARM 00213 IS ISSUED. AT THE END OF A 90 SECOND CAGE, BIT 2<newline>OF IMODES30 IS TESTED. IF IT IS = 1, ISS TURN-ON WAS NOT PRESENT FOR THE ENTIRE 90 SECONDS. IN THAT CASE, IF<newline>THE ISS TURN-ON REQUEST IS PRESENT THE 90 SECOND WAIT IS REPEATED, OTHERWISE NO ACTION OCCURS UNLESS A PROGRAM<newline>WAS WAITING FOR THE INITIALIZATION IN WHICH CASE THE PROGRAM IS GIVEN AN IMUSTALL ERROR RETURN. IF THE DELAY<newline>WENT PROPERLY, THE ISS DELAY OUTBIT IS SENT AND THE ICDU'S ZEROED. A TASK IS INITIATED TO REMOVE THE PIPA FAIL<newline>INHIBIT BIT IN 10.24 SECONDS. IF A MISSION PROGRAM WAS WAITING IT IS INFORMED VIA ENDIMU.<newline>AT PROCTNON, IF ONLY ISS OPERATE IS PRESENT (OPONLY), THE CDU'S ARE ZEROED UNLESS THE PLATFORM IS IN COARSE<newline>ALIGN (= GIMBAL LOCK HERE) OR A MISSION PROGRAM IS USING THE IMU (IMUSEFLG = 1).<newline>CALLING SEQUENCE: T4RUPT EVERY 480 MILLISECONDS AFTER IMUMON.<newline>JOBS OR TASKS INITIATED: 1) ENDTNON, 90 SECONDS AFTER CAGING STARTED. 2) ISSUP, 4 SECONDS AFTER CAGING DONE.<newline>3) PFAILOK, 10.24 SECONDS AFTER INITIALIZATION COMPLETED. 4) UNZ2, 320 MILLISECONDS AFTER ZEROING<newline>STARTED.<newline>SUBROUTINES CALLED: CAGESUB, CAGESUB2, ZEROICDU, ENDIMU, IMUBAD, NOATTOFF, SETISSW, VARDELAY.<newline>ERASABLE INITIALIZATION: SEE IMUMON.<newline>ALARMS: PROGRAM ALARM 00213 IF ISS TURN-ON REQUESTED WITHOUT ISS OPERATE.<newline>EXIT: ENDTNON EXITS TO C33TEST. TASKS HAVING TO DO WITH INITIALIZATION EXIT AS FOLLOWS: MISSION PROGRAM<newline>WAITING AND INITIALIZATION COMPLETE, EXIT TO ENDIMU, MISSION PROGRAM WAITING AND INITIALIZATION FAILED, EXIT TO<newline>IMUBAD, IMU NOT IN USE, EXIT TO TASKOVER.<newline>OUTPUT: ISS INITIALIZED.
